+From 472075a589ae3a26927b4ae8882c2b6c662fe713 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: Michael Lerman <mlerman@ironscales.com>
+Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 22:08:43 +0300
+Subject: [PATCH 1/3] refactor: land capturecast remediation plan (phases 1-6)
+MIME-Version: 1.0
+Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
+Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
+
+Phase 1 — Build hygiene & CI
+- Untrack build artifacts (background.js, page bundles, dist/, jest-output.json, worktrees/, test-results/) and extend .gitignore.
+- Replace unit-tests.yml with ci.yml that runs lint + build + unit + e2e.
+- Add build-prerequisite section to README; bump package.json to 0.2.1 to match manifest.
+
+Phase 2 — Live correctness bugs
+- Lowercase state names in overlay.js and recovery.js to match the XState machine.
+- Drop legacy STATE_*/VALID_TRANSITIONS from src/messages.js; tighten schemas (add code/mimeType, require TAB_CLOSING.tabId, add RECORDER_ERROR).
+- recovery.js sends recordingId (not id) for RECOVERY_DISCARD/RESUME.
+- Remove duplicate validation + rate-limit block from RecordingService.handleMessage (kept only in background.ts).
+- Loosen stopRecording guard to accept starting/stopping in addition to recording.
+- Remove dead second injectOverlay call (context.overlayTabId was never set).
+- Wire RECONCILE into the actor via new RecordingService.reconcile(snapshot).
+- Replace hardcoded indexedDB.open(DB, 2) in offscreen.js with shared DB_VERSION.
+
+Phase 3 — Codebase consolidation (src/ canonical)
+- Move root utilities into src/lib/: chunkStorage, recording, cleanup, db, db-shared, storage-utils, media-recorder-utils, constants.
+- Move page entry points into src/entries/: popup, consent, recorder, offscreen, preview, recordings, overlay, recovery, diagnostics.
+- Reconcile divergent error-codes.js / logger.js pairs (keep src/ shapes); delete root duplicates.
+- Extract single canonical openDB() into src/lib/db-shared.js; delete the 5+ copies.
+- Extend esbuild.config.js to bundle background (ESM), pages (ESM, flattened to root), and overlay (IIFE).
+- Update import paths repo-wide and refresh jest.config.js coverage globs.
+
+Phase 4 — Test coverage
+- Port recordingMachine.test.js to XState v5 createActor API; cover happy path, error/save-timeout/reconcile transitions, and TAB_CLOSING/UUID guards.
+- Add recordingService.test.js with mock ChromeAPI; cover startRecording, stopRecording, data routing, reconcile, and the reset hook.
+- Delete tests/unit/cdp.test.js (CDP feature not shipped; no debugger permission).
+- Add node:crypto randomUUID polyfill in tests/unit/setup.js so jsdom can run the machine.
+
+Phase 5 — Repo cleanup
+- Move keep-worthy docs (CRUSH, MIGRATION_GUIDE, SERVICE_WORKER_ANALYSIS, STORAGE_FAILURE_MATRIX, TROUBLESHOOTING, XSTATE_IMPLEMENTATION, prd) into docs/.
+- Delete one-off agent run artifacts (CODE_REVIEW, FIXES_*, FINAL_SUMMARY, FLOW_ANALYSIS, PERMISSIONS_ANALYSIS, IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY*, TEST_RESULTS).
+- Strip JSON block comments from manifest.json; move rationale into docs/permissions.md.
+- popup.html now exposes mic/system-audio checkboxes; popup.js forwards real flags to consent page.
+
+Phase 6 — Hardening
+- consent.html and recovery.html now load their scripts with type="module".
+- Expand overlay protected-URL list (view-source:, file:, chromewebstore.google.com); tighten PDF regex.
+- Move failedChunkCount + saveChunkWithRetry into the createMediaRecorder closure so concurrent recorders don't share state; remove module-level getters and update callers to use the onStop extra.failedChunks value.
+
+Verification: pnpm run build clean; ./node_modules/.bin/eslint . --ext .js → 0 errors (4 pre-existing test warnings); pnpm run test:unit → 235 passed across 14 suites.
+Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
